---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import FunctionPlotter from '../../../components/diagrams/FunctionPlotter.svelte';
---

<Layout title="Statistics" lang="en" backHref="/explore-math/en/grade-10/" backLabel="← Grade 10">
	<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Statistics</h1>
	<p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-8">Analyze data with mean, median and deviation</p>
	<section class="prose max-w-none">
		<h2>Describing Data</h2>
		<p>Mean, median and standard deviation are the three most important measures.</p>
		<h3>🧪 Experiment</h3>
		<p>Normal distribution with varying spread:</p>
	</section>
	<FunctionPlotter client:visible fn={(x, s) => Math.exp(-x*x/(2*s*s)) / (s*Math.sqrt(2*Math.PI))} fnLabel="Normal Distribution" showSlider={true} sliderLabel="σ" sliderMin={0.5} sliderMax={2} sliderStep={0.1} xMin={-5} xMax={5} yMin={0} yMax={1} />
	<section class="prose max-w-none mt-8">
		<h3>💡 Key Measures</h3>
		<ul><li>Mean x̄ = sum ÷ count</li><li>Median = middle value (sorted)</li><li>Standard deviation σ = spread around mean</li><li>68% of data within ±1σ</li></ul>
	</section>
</Layout>
